		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://wkossen.nl/weblog/?p=48</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[I recently responded to a question on LinkedIN discussiongroup. The person who asked the question was becoming doubtful of the added value architecture can have in agile projects. I want to share my answer here, so here goes:
Architecture can function in an agile approach, but it depends much on two things:

the ability of the architect [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I recently responded to a question on <a title="LinkedIN" href="http://www.linkedin.com" target="_blank">LinkedIN discussiongroup</a>. The person who asked the question was becoming doubtful of the added value architecture can have in agile projects. I want to share my answer here, so here goes:</p>
<p>Architecture can function in an agile approach, but it depends much on two things:</p>
<ol>
<li>the ability of the architect to work highly interactive and very much directed towards the organisation and it&#8217;s stakeholders</li>
<li>the maturity of the organisation in working agile and using architecture.</li>
</ol>
<p>The &#8216;old-fashioned&#8217; business architect doesn&#8217;t work fast. He (or she) wants to first map out the organisation, their processes etc, and then start drafting an architecture for it or it&#8217;s systems. That&#8217;s a slow process by nature. It doesn&#8217;t work well with agile development where you &#8216;design as you go&#8217; in a highly interactive fashion. You need a &#8216;new breed&#8217; of architect to deal with that.</p>
<p>Also there is the need for strong architectural awareness with the developers and the stakeholders of the project. If they don&#8217;t see the need or benefits of architecture, they will never really &#8216;like&#8217; their presence and appreciate their added value. at the same time, the architect can&#8217;t be successfull because he needs the help from the stakeholders to create the architecture in the first place&#8230;</p>
<p>It can be done, but it&#8217;s not &#8217;standard&#8217;&#8230;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.mylivesignature.com" target="_blank"><img src="http://signatures.mylivesignature.com/85709/wkossen/4c685b3de1f98bc3665afa55cc11559d.png" border="0" /></a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
